# Post-Change Model Audit (Dan standing preference)

After **every substantive code or config change** in this session, perform a **brief model audit** before reporting done. Dan wants confidence the cheapest capable model was used вҖ” and verification when a higher tier was warranted.

## Default worker

**Composer 2.5 Fast** implements all T0/T1/T2 work inline. Do not escalate for routine UI, service logic, or multi-file features unless a trigger below applies.

## Security gate timing

Run the Sonnet 4.6 security gate **before pushing** вҖ” not after commit. If Sonnet returns HIGH risk, fix before `git push origin main`. **Merged on main:** use commit-range diff (`git diff <commit>^..<commit>`); security-review subagent required before claiming PASS (detail: LIBRARIAN_LESSONS В§ process-agents #10).

## Security gate invocation (mandatory вҖ” authoritative)

**Model authority:** `.cursor/rules/security-review-gate.mdc` вҖ” **only** `claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking`. Composer 2.5 must **never** perform or substitute for the security gate.

Invoke **only** via **one** `Task` call per ship cycle. **Never** self-report "Sonnet PASS" from Composer inline review.

**Required Task parameters (all mandatory вҖ” never omit `model`):**

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| `subagent_type` | `"security-review"` |
| `model` | `"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking"` |
| `readonly` | `true` |
| `run_in_background` | `false` (await completion before push) |
| `description` | `"Security Review"` |

**Prompt shape** вҖ” per `review-security` SKILL.md (workspace override in `composer-orchestrator.mdc` В§ Security gate):

```text
Full Repository Path: <absolute repo path>
Diff: <"branch changes" | "uncommitted changes">
Custom Instructions: <only when user gave specific review instructions>
```

Default `Diff` before first push: `uncommitted changes`. After merge on main without prior gate: `branch changes` with commit-range context in Custom Instructions.

**Hard stops:**

- **NEVER** push CF / auth / Firestore-rules changes until the security-review subagent returns a verdict.
- **NEVER** launch duplicate security Tasks in the same turn (exactly one gate Task).
- **NEVER** substitute Composer self-review if the subagent fails вҖ” retry once per SKILL; if it fails twice, **STOP ship** and report blocker (subagent id + error); verdict = **NOT RUN**.
- **NEVER** write PASS/MEDIUM/HIGH without the subagent's returned id in the completion report.
- **NEVER** use Composer 2.5 (or any model other than `claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking`) for `security-review` вҖ” see `security-review-gate.mdc`.

**Subagent failure:** one retry with corrected invocation per SKILL; second failure вҶ’ stop ship, report blocker, verdict **NOT RUN** вҖ” do not push.

## When to audit with a higher model (Sonnet 4.6 via Task subagent)

Run a short review **only if** the change (before push) touched any of:

| Trigger | Review focus |
|---------|----------------|
| `backend-write-critical` (Firestore rules, CF write paths, schema migrations) | Security, authz, data integrity |
| Auth / route guards / Firestore read paths on protected routes | Leaks, bypass, wrong actorType |
| Genuinely ambiguous high-stakes decision already implemented | Correctness vs intent |
| Composer uncertainty or failed first fix on T2+ work | Root cause + fix quality |

**Opus 4.6** вҖ” locked fallback only if Sonnet flags HIGH risk Composer cannot resolve.

## When Composer 2.5 alone is sufficient (no Sonnet pass)

- T0: `ui-component`, `css-restyle`, `docs-update`
- T1: `multi-file-feature`, `type-refactor`, `service-logic` **without** rules/auth changes
- T2: same as T1 when no auth/Firestore-read escalation trigger fired
- Pure Q&A, typos, read-only investigation
- Parallel read-only scouts (no Sonnet audit required)

## Audit output (mandatory in assistant reply)

Complete the **ship loop** (`ship-loop.mdc`) before declaring done for **code or config changes** вҖ” commit, push, and deploy must succeed (or deploy failure reported clearly). Read-only audits and rules/docs-only work: commit + push when applicable; no gh-pages deploy unless the bundle changed.

### Low-risk exemption (no full table)

For read-only audits, docs-only updates, rules-only updates, and other T0 non-product work, the final report does **not** need the full model audit table unless model choice or escalation was material. A short line is enough вҖ” e.g. `Model routing: T0 docs/rules; no escalation`.

End substantive **code/config** work with a compact block:

```
### Model audit
| Change | Archetype | Tier | Worker | Scouts parallel? | Escalation review? | Verdict |
|--------|-----------|------|--------|-------------------|-------------------|---------|
| вҖҰ | вҖҰ | вҖҰ | Composer 2.5 | Yes / No / N/A | No / security-review вҶ’ see below | OK / note |
```

**Escalation review row** (when security gate triggered) вҖ” replace vague "Sonnet вҶ’ PASS" with:

```
security-review subagent id: <id from Task return>
model: claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking
verdict: PASS | MEDIUM | HIGH | NOT RUN
finding: <one-line summary from subagent, or "none" / failure reason>
```

- **Verdict OK** вҖ” tier and worker matched the work; no review needed (Escalation review? = No).
- **Verdict note** вҖ” security-review subagent found an issue; fix or document before done.
- **No subagent id** вҶ’ verdict must be **NOT RUN**, not PASS вҖ” do not push CF/auth/rules.
- If escalation review was required but not run, **do not declare done** вҖ” run it first.

